abstracts.cdata!:
The Fourth Highway Project comprises:
            (a) construction, reconstruction or improvement of (i) five
            feeder roads totalling 158 km; (ii) 995 km of tea collection
            roads; (iii) 429 km of access roads in settlement areas; and
            (iv) three trunk roads sections totalling 71 km; (b)
            construction and equipping of two vehicle weighing stations;
            and (c) retention of consultants for completion of
            engineering and supervision of construction as required.
